{
  "thag4.9:0.1": "Verses of the Senior Monks 4.9 ",
  "thag4.9:0.2": "The Book of the Fours ",
  "thag4.9:0.3": "Chapter One ",
  "thag4.9:0.4": "Candana ",
  "thag4.9:1.1": "Covered over with gold, ",
  "thag4.9:1.2": "surrounded by all her maids, ",
  "thag4.9:1.3": "with my son upon her hip, ",
  "thag4.9:1.4": "my wife came to me. ",
  "thag4.9:2.1": "I saw her coming, ",
  "thag4.9:2.2": "the mother of my son, ",
  "thag4.9:2.3": "adorned with jewelry and all dressed up, ",
  "thag4.9:2.4": "like a snare of death laid down. ",
  "thag4.9:3.1": "Then the realization ",
  "thag4.9:3.2": "came upon me—",
  "thag4.9:3.3": "the danger became clear, ",
  "thag4.9:3.4": "and I was firmly disillusioned. ",
  "thag4.9:4.1": "Then my mind was freed—",
  "thag4.9:4.2": "see the excellence of the teaching! ",
  "thag4.9:4.3": "I’ve attained the three knowledges ",
  "thag4.9:4.4": "and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions. "
}